I need to identify the specific line items and values representing capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares, both at the beginning and end of the period.

Looking at the balance sheet, I can see that shareholder capital contributions are typically shown in the "Paid-in Capital" line item, which represents the amount that shareholders have invested in the company by purchasing shares.

In the provided balance sheet, I can see:
- "Paid-in Capital" had an initial amount of 13,000,000.00 on 2023-12-31
- "Paid-in Capital" had an end amount of 13,000,000.00 on 2024-02-05

The value remained the same over this period, indicating that there were no additional capital contributions or returns of capital to shareholders during this time.
